content:
New and Changed Lightning Web Components

Build UI easily with these new and changed components.

Changed Lightning Web Components

These components have changed.

lightning-combobox
You can now use the Tab or Enter key to select combobox elements.
The string value of the combobox label is now used on the aria-label attribute on the input and button elements.
spinner-active—When this attribute is present, role=”presentation” is replaced by role=”option” on the wrapping div element for lightning-spinner.
required—The error message reads out on every focus.

lightning-datatable
Unsaved cells have new colors to improve contrast.
Assistive text is appended to unsaved cells in addition to contrasting color.
Custom data types support keyboard navigation. Set data-navigation=”enable” and tab-index={internalTabIndex} on custom elements.
aria-describedby—An ID of an element that provides a description for the table element.
data-navigation—Set value to “enable” on custom elements to enable keyboard navigation.
tabindex—Set value to {internalTabIndex} on custom elements to enable keyboard navigation.
aria-selected—When you specify hide-checkbox-column, aria-selected is removed from all tr elements.

lightning-helptext
You can now dismiss the helptext tooltip on focus by pressing the Escape key.
Moving the mouse into the helptext tooltip doesn’t make the tooltip disappear.

lightning-input
Set role=”status” and aria-live=”polite” to set error messages on input elements.
aria-live—Set aria-live=”polite” to set input error messages.
type=”color”
Hue slider now represents the updated value set from the input field.
Screen readers now state “Current Color: None Selected” when no color is selected.

lightning-input-address
show-compact-address—When this attribute is present, the street field is rendered as two separate inputs instead of a single textarea.
subpremise—The value for the subpremise field. The maximum length is 80 characters.
subpremise-label—The label for the subpremise field, which is visible only when using show-compact-address.

lightning-progress-indicator
role=”presentation” when type=”path”.
role=”listitem” when type=”base”.

lightning-progress-step
This component now uses a div with tabindex=”0” instead of a button.
label—A step with an error now appends “Error” to the label for assistive text.

lightning-select
aria-describedby—The ID of an element or elements on the page that provides an accessible description for the select element.
aria-labelledby—The ID of an element or elements on the page that provides an accessible name for the select element.

lightning-textarea
aria-labelledby—The ID of an element or elements on the page that provides an accessible name for the textarea element.

lightning-tree

Data can now be added dynamically through the tree component whenever it’s loaded by using the key and expand properties in the change event.
title: Salesforce Summer '24 Release Notes
